Elytra dorsally almost glabrous, slightly shining, in dorsal view oval-elongate, in lateral view slightly vaulted (EL: 4.40–4.80 mm , EW: 2.60–2.80 mm , EL/EW: 1.70–1.72). Elytra slightly convex, widest at middle of moderately rounded sides, not fused but suture ill defined. Humeri protruding, angular and toothed (
Fig. 1g
). Wings absent. Each elytron with nine complete striae; seventh stria raised and prominent particularly at humeri. Interstriae convex, with 10 to 20 punctures and with sparse thin setae. Elytral declivity from 60 to 75 degrees.
